From: "Randy R. Wall" <rrw@ecst.csuchico.edu>

> 
> Sorry if this has been asked before. There is no mention in the manual
> (IM3.0 Amiga) of a facility in the forms editor (two former view) to copy
> only part of a slice, I was wondering if there is a way to do this. I've
> got a car-body.form coming together and want to copy the sills and
> leave the upper bodywork intact.

No I don't believe so, you would have to go into the Detail Editor to do 
this, and once you save it back out it will not reload into the forms 
editor for more editing. You could delete all the pionts of that area, 
buy selecting Right Amiga-D and DragBox and draging the box over the 
points you want to get rid of..but you will need to remove any keys you 
may have on them, or it will not let you delete them..

=RRW=




