> Hi people,
> 
> the big problem with slice is that it also uses edges which have a zero angle
> 
> in a slice, this makes a slice a bit messy and results in an object that has
> to much faces/edges/points.
> If this would be fixed (I posted the problem to Mike on compuserve) slicing
> would probably also be succesful more often.
> 
> Grtz, Milan.
People generally forget that SLICE is very complex topological 
operation. Computers can't "see" the form of objects, so the 
algorithms have to compute the models as a whole, which is extremely 
difficult

