@node IML-128 " MSG-128  Subject: "Slice" of crow"

Subject: "Slice" of crow
Date: Thu, 11 Aug 1994 14:39:47 -0700
From: bmolsen@bvu-lads.loral.com (Brad Molsen)

        Hello all,
                Two days ago on this list I made the following statement
concerning my complaint about the intermittent reliability of the slice
function in Imagine.
        "If I had a dollar for every minute that I sat diddling my mouse to
try to reposition my slice to alleviate "an edge is to close to an edge" I
could buy
Wavefront!!!"
                Well, coincidently right after posting that message, I ran
into a friend in the company lunch room who has Wavefront (at a total cost
of $11000.00). Full of self rightious indignation , I asked him how well
the Wavefront equivilent of slice worked. "It Sucks", he said. He then went
on to tell me that it works intermittently also and that he has to
reposition his "slicer" several times to get it to work right too. He
explained a situation that he had run into the night before using this
function and that he never did get it to work correctly! I told him that
once when trying to cut eye holes into a snakehead object, only one could
be done and that I had to resort to deleting the half of the head without
the eye and then I copied, mirrored, and joined both halves back together
to achieve a two eyed snake. He responded with "You can mirror?" I was
shocked, apparently he can't. Were talking 11 thousand dollars and he can't
mirror! Now don't get me wrong for that kind of money I'm sure there are
many things his program can do that Imagine can't but, apparently this
slice type function is one slippery character, even in that price range!
        I asked another fellow worker who owns Strata for the Mac how his
slice type function works. (He paid approx. $900.00 for his software.) He
said that he can't take an obscure cookie cutter shape and have it cut out
the same shape from a 3d object!
                I received 2 responses the next day on the list about my
post from Daniel 'Mega, and Milan Polle explaining the techical difficulty
of successful 100% slicing, which were very enlightening and informative.
Not being technically inclined, I needed this info to appreciate what I was
asking for and also to appreciate the powerful package we all have in
Imagine.
                Lastly, I recieved a VERY nice email from Mike Halvorson
regarding my complaint. Having not asked his permission to post his
response, suffice it to say that he and his people are working to make
slice more robust and will continue to do so. Thanks Mike!
                Sorry, for taking up so much bandwidth about this and I'm
sure in some cases I'm preaching to the choir but, for those of you who see
the Imagine glass as only half full and complain about it not having this
or that one doesn't have to look to far to see that for the money it's the
best in the market place.
                Now, if you'll excuse me, I have a plate of crow waiting for me.

                                        regards,

xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
        Almond rocca?!! Ahhh..no thanks, I have a cat!

Brad Molsen c/o  LORAL                          bmolsen@bvu-lads.loral.com

13810 SE Eastgate Way Suite 500                 (206) 957-3230
Bellevue, Wa 98005                              Fax: (206) 746-1335




