@node IML-216 " MSG-216  Subject: RE: VOTES FOR IMAG"

Subject: RE: VOTES FOR IMAG
Date: Wed, 17 Aug 94 22:18:37 -0300
From: greg.tsadilas@hofbbs.com

 > - when you select "pick points" and redraw, all the
 > other objects but the picked one disapear. I think
 > it's bad because you may want to change the
 > shape of the object based on other object's position
 > or shape. I think it's better to redraw them in a
 > discrete color.

Thats easy.  Select the object you want to edit, then MULTI-PICK the objects
you want to be used as reference objects.  Then enter points mode, edit and
refresh the screen to your hears content.  The multi-selected objects will
redraw with the object you are editing.

I like this method, because I can choose which objects I want displayed while I
am editing.  It not only speeds up redraws, but there is less clutter.

-GreG



