@node IML-226 " MSG-226  Subject: Re: ISL 3.0"

Subject: Re: ISL 3.0
Date: Thu, 18 Aug 94 13:30:20 PDT
From: John.T.Grieggs@jpl.nasa.gov (John T. Grieggs)

> 	What IS ISL?
> 
ISL is the Imagine Staging Language.  It lets you decompile staging files
into a nice, easy-to-hack ASCII form.  You can modify ISL files, then use
another part of the ISL package to generate a new staging file containing
your mods.  You can also programmatically generate ISL.

It's not quite as nice as built-on AREXX, but it's a heck of a lot better
than nothing at all.  :-)

The current version, 2.0, only works on stages up through Imagine 2.0, but
it does handle PC stages.  The upcoming version, 3.0, will handle Imagine
3.0 stages, and eventually will run on the PC as well.  Since Imagine 3.0
can read and promote Imagine 2.0 staging files, you can use ISL with it
now, in a limited manner.

> 	Ed
> 
> /****************************************************************************/

> /* Ed Phillips  flaregun@strauss.udel.edu      University of Delaware       */

> /* Jr Systems Programmer  (302) 831-6082    IT/Network and Systems Services */

> /****************************************************************************/

> 
_john



