> To morph between two objects with the same number of points and faces, 
> put the first object in frame 1 in Action. Add the second object on 
> frames 2-50 on the same actor bar, and VOILA! A morph! Hope this helps...

Sounds good for 3.0. But this will not work in 2.0 which is what the 
person wanted to know how to do. It will if he inputs 48 into the 
Transition frame count. Something that has been removed from 3.0. If he 
did this without using Transision frame count in 2.0 the object would 
change to OBJ2 in frame 2 and not morph at all. Just mentioning it for 
any others out there with 2.0 wondering how to do this.

