@node IML-324 " MSG-324  Subject: Re: Nebula Texture."

Subject: Re: Nebula Texture.
Date: Fri, 2 Sep 94 11:11:17 +0100
From: milan@valkieser.nl (Milan Polle)

Hi David,

I think the whole problem lies in the fact that your object doesn't 
have any front faces.
The way I think fog works is it measures the distance between two fog faces
one ray hits (just like refraction with glass). So if the ray only hits one
fog face, nothing happens.

Hope this helps.

Let your imagination run wild,

Milan (milan@valkieser.nl)

